132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1968
H.P. 1312 House of Representatives, May 13, 2025
An Act to Amend the Laws Regarding Legislative Reimbursement
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MOONEN of Portland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 3 MRSA §2, 4th ¶, as amended by PL 2023, c. 2, §3, is further amended to
3 read:
4 Except as provided in this section, each member of the Senate and House of
5 Representatives is entitled to the travel-related expenses of a meal allowance in the amount
6 of $50 set by the Legislative Council and a housing allowance in the amount of $70 set by
7 the Legislative Council for each day in attendance at sessions of the Legislature and for
8 each day the member occupies overnight accommodations away from home either
9 immediately preceding or immediately following attendance at daily sessions of the
10 Legislature. The presiding officers may establish reasonable policies regarding allowances
11 for meals and overnight accommodations for the day immediately preceding the session,
12 which may include policies regarding whether an allowance is paid, whether the full
13 amount or a portion of the statutory allowance set by the Legislative Council is paid and
14 whether receipts are required. In lieu of the meal and housing allowance, each member is
15 entitled to a daily meal allowance in the amount of $50 set by the Legislative Council and
16 actual daily mileage. Each member of the Senate also receives an annual allowance for
17 constituent services in the amount of $2,000, $1,300 in January and $700 in the month
18 following adjournment of the regular session. Each member of the House of
19 Representatives also receives an annual allowance for constituent services in the amount
20 of $1,500, $1,005 in January and $495 in the month following adjournment of the regular
21 session. Notwithstanding this section, during the first regular session of each legislative
22 biennium, a member of the Senate or the House of Representatives may elect to receive the
23 first payment of the annual allowance for constituent services in December following
24 convening of the Legislature by notifying the Executive Director of the Legislative Council
25 in the manner prescribed by the executive director. The Executive Director of the
26 Legislative Council shall inform Legislators of the choice available for payment of the
27 allowance for constituent services in the first year of the legislative biennium and of any
28 tax implications associated with exercising that choice. To set the amount of an allowance
29 under this paragraph, at least 6 members of the Legislative Council must vote in favor of
30 the allowance at the beginning of the first regular session of a legislative biennium. The
31 amount of an allowance set by the Legislative Council under this paragraph may not exceed
32 the regular federal per diem rate for lodging, meals and incidental expenses applicable to
33 that allowance.
34 Sec. 2. 3 MRSA §2, 11th ¶, as amended by PL 2023, c. 2, §5, is further amended
35 to read:
36 The President of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of Representatives, the floor
37 leaders and their assistants and members of a committee, with the approval of the President
38 of the Senate or the Speaker of the House of Representatives as to members of a committee,
39 may also meet on days when the Legislature is not in daily session at any convenient
40 location within the State. Each member of the Senate and House of Representatives is
41 entitled to receive $55 for every day's attendance when meetings or daily sessions are held
42 and the travel-related expenses of a meal allowance in the amount of $50 set by the
43 Legislative Council and a housing allowance whereby actual lodging expenses will be
44 reimbursed at the single-room rate, as long as a receipt is submitted to the Executive
45 Director of the Legislative Council for each day in attendance at such meetings or daily
